The social card of the resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The changes envisage the preservation of the travel allowance in public passenger transport.
Since September 24, the order of the organization of preferential passage of citizens using the social map of the inhabitants of the Ivanov region has changed.
According to the press service of the Government of Russia on the Ivanovsk region, the changes provide for the preservation of the travel allowance in public passenger transport and bring the scheme of mutual calculations on the social map in accordance with the requirements of the Federal Law No. 161 of the FZ "On National Payment System".
At the same time, the social card of the resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
Accordingly, the conditions of its application are changed.
Thus, the limit of replenishment is now set not in travel as before, but in the amount of money, with the preservation of winter and summer periods - not more than 400 rubles, in the summer period - not more than 800 rubles for the current month.
Now the holders of the social card on the receipts issued in the transport will need to track not the number of remaining trips, but the rest of the cash.
The cost of a preferential pass for citizens will be 1/2 of the tariff in effect with the carrier.
The remaining half of the cost of the trip is reimbursed by the regional budget.
The schedule of refilling the social card with cash remains the same – in the period from the 24th of the previous month to the 23rd of the current month.
The new order of passage on the social map will have a number of advantages.
Thus, it is possible to keep a detailed account of the spending of money on a social card with accuracy to the copeek.
In addition, there is the possibility of returning deposited but unused funds.
We also add that the scheme of mutual settlements with carriers becomes transparent, since now half of the cost of travel is paid by the citizen, and exactly the same amount is reimbursed by the carrier budget.
No commission will be charged when depositing money on the card.
In turn, Vasily Silkin, Deputy Head of the Department of Road Economy and Transport of the Ivanovo Region, said that in 2014 there were more than 33 million trips in the region using a social card, in 2015 - almost 25 million trips.
More than 470 million rubles are provided in the regional budget for granting preferential travel to citizens using a social card.
As of 1 September, the amount of compensation for these purposes amounted to more than 312 million rubles.
