The World Bank has granted Ukraine a $500 million loan.
The World Bank has approved a new loan project for Ukraine in the amount of $500 million for the development of the financial sector.
This was reported by the press service of the international organization.
“The new funding will support a number of priority measures to carry out reforms in the banking sector in response to the financial crisis in Ukraine,” the statement said.
