The blacksmiths of the script of the film "Citizen Kane" will be put on sale.
Representatives of the auction house Profiles in History announced plans to put on sale a black version of the script of the film "Citizen Cain", which is considered one of the best works of director, screenwriter and actor Orson Wells.
The auction will begin in the city of Calabasas on September 29, it will present three black versions of the script, the estimated cost of each of them is $20-30 thousand.
The first of the Negroes, written in 1940 by Herman Mankevich, is the earliest script to be found in private collections? and titled "American" - such a working name was in the film.
The second draft is a more complete version of the script, and the third is the final plan of the film.
