The comfortable rate for an investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the lending market for small and medium-sized businesses in January-April of this year fell by 40%.
What do you think is the situation today?
After the panicked moods of the end of 2014 - the beginning of 2015, the volume of loans to SMEs decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Loans under 25-30% per annum were not beneficial to anyone.
If in the past the bank could place all its possible problems at a higher rate in the future, from delays to non-refunds, then now it is impossible to do it: bets and so cloudy.
For businesses, the current level of SME loan rates is uncomfortable.
For a large part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their return on investment.
The rate of 10-13% would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and form attractive returns on them.
To what extent do you believe that the demand for loans is satisfied?
After the decline of the central bank interest rate, the situation improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, the business does not understand the prospects of its development and future income.
Today, business has one solution: it is necessary to learn to work, focusing on the current economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, to monitor the movement of funds.
At the same time, in the presence of financial resources, it is worth using new technologies to modernize the equipment, reduce the cost of production and energy supply.
All of this, in the end, allows the company to make products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What major trends in the SME lending market will strengthen and influence its development by the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for the average rate reduction will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator is showing consistency in the issue of the key rate reduction.
However, a radical fall in the price of loans for SMEs is not worth waiting for.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes it necessary to raise the interest rate to get real income.
In addition, the value of money in Russia will remain high even as the central bank’s interest rates fall.
If we talk about the level of delay, then traditionally small and medium-sized businesses, limited in both the ability to replenish funds and in the options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly pose a greater risk to creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the economy of the country.
