The parties were given mandates.
Yesterday, the electoral commission of Nizhny Novgorod summed up the results of the elections in the city duma in the municipal district, distributing 12 parliamentary mandates played on party lists.
Traditionally, many complaints of violations during the elections were heard by representatives of the KPRF, who accused the poller of “covering forgeries”.
The opposition’s comments were not accepted.
At the same time, the elector rejected the party "Communists of Russia" in the organization of a referendum on the cancellation of the fee for the renovation of multi-apartment houses.
The municipal constituency officially presented the results of the elections in the Pride of Nizhny Novgorod in the municipal constituency.
In total, 1.03 million people were included in the lists of voters in Nizhny Novgorod, 746.7 thousand ballot papers were issued in the district commissions, and 268,000 voters voted in the elections.
More than 11.7 thousand bulletins were declared invalid and 24 were lost.
Yesterday, 12 mandates were distributed among the political parties depending on the votes they received.
According to the lists of "United Russia" six MP seats in pride are entrusted to Dmitry Svatkovsky, Dmitry Krasnov, Vasily Shupranov, Elizabet Solonchenko, Vyacheslav Rasteryaev and Igor Nagorny.
The only mandate of the LDPR was received by the leader of the party Vladimir Zhirinovsky.
The two mandates of the CPRF are divided between Vladimir Bulanov and Deputy of the State Duma Alexander Tarnaev.
The three mandates of “Just Russia” are given to Alexander Razumovsky, Igor Bogdanov and Mikhail Shalugin.
Now, within five days, these candidates must determine whether they will work as deputies in the city council: in the event of a resignation, he moves to the next candidate on the party list.
Chairman of the Horizbirkom Aleksandr Makeev told the members of the commission that he is introducing the task of "sending telegrams to Zhirinovsky and others" on the subject of refusal of mandates.
When the protocol on the results of the elections was approved, the representatives of the CPRF declared multiple violations.
A member of the Horizbirkom with the right of a consultative vote from the CPRF Leonid Krasnokutsky proposed not to recognize the results of the vote in the four districts No.21-24, recalling that at the order of the head of the administration of the Sormovsky district, the entrance to the administration building was closed.
Neither the deputies of the State of Udma, nor the candidates themselves, nor the observers, could enter for a long time, and the resonant scandal with the storming of the door of the administration was shown on television.
At the meetings of the district commissions, all observers and members of the commissions with the right to vote had the opportunity to attend.
The head stopped accessing them only when the vote was over and the local commissions had not yet come to issue their ballots.
This was done in order to prevent various provocations.
“Then the chapter was corrected, and at all the meetings the interested persons could be present,” said the member of the mountain range Natalya Andryushin.
The Communists objected that in the blocked administration building more than four hours illegally detained deputy zak of the district assembly Ludmil Aristov, about which a statement was sent to the investigative committee.
The opposition was also outraged that in a number of UICs on election day began sealing the ballots at 6-7 a.m., putting out bulletins for early voting.
At the same time, the members of the committees with the right to vote and the observers were not notified, so they arrived already at the beginning of the election at 8 a.m.
The Communists are confident that in the morning hours before the opening of the polling stations, they could uncontrollably throw bulletins into the urns.
