The Duma introduced a bill on the indexation of pensions taking into account the increase in prices.
The State Duma has introduced a bill that provides for the indexation of social pensions annually from 1 February, taking into account the increase in prices.
The author of the document - deputy of "Just Russia" Alexander Lomakin-Romantsev - also proposes to carry out additional indexation of pensions on April 1, if the rate of growth of the subsistence minimum exceeds the rate of increase in prices for goods and services.
The indexation of pensions, according to the current legislation, is carried out annually from April 1, taking into account the rate of growth of the minimum living pensioner in the Russian Federation for the past year.
The bill, introduced in the lower house, provides for the introduction of the indexation of social pensions, taking into account the pace of the growth of consumer prices.
At the same time, the first indexing is postponed to February 1, and the second is carried out on April 1.
