Where can I leave a review of the work of the court clerk in Murmansk?
The Office of the Federal Service of Judicial Officers in the Murmansk Region reported that in order to improve the work on the protection of the rights and legitimate interests of citizens and organizations in the department there is a book of reviews and proposals.
In it, citizens can leave a record of the quality of work of the judicial assistants and other management officials, information about shortcomings in the work, as well as express their suggestions and wishes.
In the management, a copy of the book of reviews and offers is in the central hall, in a special pocket in a visible and accessible place at the pass to the building.
In the structural departments of management, the book is in the office.
Taking into account the nature of the withdrawal or proposal, if necessary, a written reply shall be sent to its initiator.
Xi Jinping urges to make the economy more open to the world
The economy needs to become more open to the world to boost its growth, President Xi Jinping said Tuesday in an address to a group facing the task of leading reforms.
“China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and developing a policy of openness,” he said, addressing the participants of the 16th meeting of the Central Leading Group on Comprehensive Deepening Reforms.
According to him, expanding openness and deepening reforms will give the economy a new impetus and vitality and provide new space for economic development.
The Leading Group adopted a number of directives, including the introduction of regulation of investor access to the market, changes to the rules of border control, the promotion of public enterprises (SOE), attracting private capital and the revision of the system of registration of residents.
According to the statement, a list of economic and manufacturing sectors not available for investment will be drawn up.
The system will be gradually decommissioned through trial programs.
This is an important step as it will give the market a more significant role in the allocation of resources, ensuring business law and increasing openness, as stated in the statement.
The government will also weaken control over the powers it has given to companies, ensuring that companies will run their own business.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions to master new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to boost local growth.
More areas will be available to private investors in order to increase the openness of the state-controlled sectors of the economy.
“The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing, as well as provide them with better conditions,” the statement said.
In addition, the procedure for applying for permanent residence permits for foreigners, or "green card", will be facilitated by optimizing the requirements and simplifying the filing process itself.
The meeting also discussed the protection of the rights of lawyers and the training of professional judges and prosecutors.
According to the official report issued after the meeting, it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Ketian and Ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli.
